WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:17.000
1. Shanghai, a beautiful city during the day, becomes even more beautiful at night. At the end of the day, both the older part of the city around the Bund and the more modern part in Pudong are full of colorful lights.

00:17.000 --> 00:23.000
The buildings, both new and old, look very different and exciting.

00:23.000 --> 00:29.000
2. If you look across the Huangpu River, you can see the beautiful oriental pearl radio.

00:29.000 --> 00:39.000
The beautiful pearl radio and TV tower and the Jinmau Tower. If you take a boat along the river, you will have a wonderful experience.

00:39.000 --> 00:52.000
3. If you like walking in the streets, try the famous Nanjing Road. There are busy shops and coffee bars and you'll see thousands of people enjoying themselves.

00:52.000 --> 01:02.000
Most of the shops close at 10pm, but at that time, tea houses are still open, where you can meet old friends and make new ones.

01:02.000 --> 01:11.000
4. If you're in Shanghai for the first time, make sure you visit Shinti-N-D, a very popular area.

01:11.000 --> 01:23.000
You can see both western buildings and Chinese buildings side by side. Most of the buildings are modern and there are shops, restaurants and coffee houses inside.

